description: The PopUpEvent class represents an event dispatched by the SkinnablePopUpContainer.

members.description:
The PopUpEvent.OPEN constant defines the value of the type property of the PopUpEvent object for an open event.

The properties of the event object have the following values:

PropertyValue
bubblesfalse
cancelablefalse
commitNot used
currentTargetThe Object that defines the event listener that handles the event. For example, if you use myButton.addEventListener() to register an event listener, myButton is the value of the currentTarget.
DataNot used
targetThe Object that dispatched the event; it is not always the Object listening for the event. Use the currentTarget property to always access the Object listening for the event.
TypePopUpEvent.OPEN

The PopUpEvent.CLOSE constant defines the value of the type property of the PopUpEvent object for an close event.

The properties of the event object have the following values:

PropertyValue
bubblesfalse
cancelablefalse
commitSpecifies whether the listener should commit the data.
currentTargetThe Object that defines the event listener that handles the event. For example, if you use myButton.addEventListener() to register an event listener, myButton is the value of the currentTarget.
DataAny data returned to the application from the SkinnablePopUpContainer.
targetThe Object that dispatched the event; it is not always the Object listening for the event. Use the currentTarget property to always access the Object listening for the event.
TypePopUpEvent.OPEN
Constructor. Only used with the PopUpEvent.CLOSE event.

values: type The event type; indicates the action that caused the event.
bubbles Specifies whether the event can bubble up the display list hierarchy.
cancelable Specifies whether the behavior associated with the event can be prevented.
commit Specifies whether the listener should commit the data from the SkinnablePopUpContainer.
data The data to commit. Only used with the PopUpEvent.CLOSE event.

members.description: Specifies whether the event listener should commit the data returned in the data property. Only used with PopUpEvent.CLOSE event.
The data to commit. Only used with PopUpEvent.CLOSE event.
